fields.title: NOPE
fields.review: Admirable for its originality and ambition even when its reach exceeds its grasp, Nope adds Spielbergian spectacle to Jordan Peele's growing arsenal.

fields.title: The Godfather Part 2
fields.review: The early life and career of Vito Corleone in 1920s New York City is portrayed, while his son, Michael, expands and tightens his grip on the family crime syndicate.

fields.title: Pulp Fiction
fields.review: The lives of two mob hitmen, a boxer, a gangster and his wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.

fields.title: Forrest Gump
fields.review: Forrest Gump is one of the best movies of all time, guaranteed. It has such a special place in my heart. The performances are just so unforgettable and never get out of your head.

fields.title: Inception
fields.review: Christopher Nolan's Inception (2010) is a complex science fiction thriller about a group of people with varying specific skills that create a perfect team of dream-sharers.

fields.title: Se7en
fields.review: Gothic, shocking, suspenseful, disturbing and clever, `Seven' marked a new beginning for director David Fincher's career.

fields.title: Parasite
fields.review: This movie is a masterpiece. It will make you belly laugh, it will chill you to the bone, and it will make you shed a tear.

fields.title: Memento
fields.review: Christopher Nolan's 'Memento' is truly a rare and exceptional achievement in modern filmmaking in that it manages to be new, fresh, hip, and exciting without ever tiring its audience out

fields.title: The Sixth Sense
fields.review: The Sixth Sense is a brilliant film, plain and simple. It is unique in that it relies on imagination and psychology to scare you and make you think twice about the world around you.

fields.title: The Truman Show
fields.review: An unassuming film that is thought provoking on so many levels, well acted and thoroughly enjoyable however you come to it
